Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 161
Edition:
Quote: Every autumn the Rocklands men had to scratch-muster the back of both Beaumont and Gladbrook for straying cattle and it was not uncommon to run across odd bunches of 'cleanskins' - unmarked cattle.
